have a drill if the health

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:40.020
department came, because
we were broke down,

00:04:40.020 --> 00:04:43.270
which is like a big no-no,
and we were in this garage.

00:04:43.270 --> 00:04:46.380
But we were selling so much
food that we were like,

00:04:46.380 --> 00:04:47.850
spilling out of the truck.

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:49.990
Like, the truck
could not contain it.

00:04:49.990 --> 00:04:54.660
So we're in this garage, and we
had like, a prep refrigerator,

00:04:54.660 --> 00:04:57.600
and these prep tables in
there, and next to that

00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:02.850
was a [INAUDIBLE] and a salt
truck for in a snow plow.

00:05:02.850 --> 00:05:05.607
And it was just like, you can't
make it up-- only in Detroit.

00:05:05.607 --> 00:05:07.690
SPEAKER: Only in Detroit,
I was just about to say.

00:05:07.690 --> 00:05:11.090
BRAD GREENHILL: Only In
Detroit, in this specific era,

00:05:11.090 --> 00:05:13.350
could that have happened.

00:05:13.350 --> 00:05:16.090
So you know, so
we'd run this drill.

00:05:16.090 --> 00:05:18.390
If the Health Department
came, shut the door,

00:05:18.390 --> 00:05:21.150
and oh, they're not here today.

00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:23.520
And we kind of got away
with it, because our truck

00:05:23.520 --> 00:05:27.180
was licensed in Royal Oak.

00:05:27.180 --> 00:05:31.545
And so it didn't really fall
under the Detroit jurisdiction.

00:05:31.545 --> 00:05:35.460
And we just had to,
like every six months,

00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.630
find a way to get
it to Royal Oak

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:41.050
to get it reinspected,
to get the thing.

