00:26:35.205 --> 00:26:36.080
BRAD GREENHILL: Yeah.

00:26:36.080 --> 00:26:43.890
Well, I was in Thailand at the
time that the fire happened.

00:26:43.890 --> 00:26:44.958
Luckily-- yeah.

00:26:44.958 --> 00:26:46.166
SPEAKER: Yeah, it wasn't you.

00:26:46.166 --> 00:26:47.850
BRAD GREENHILL:
Yeah, it wasn't me.

00:26:47.850 --> 00:26:50.700
Luckily, it was at the
tail end of my trip,

00:26:50.700 --> 00:26:52.890
so I didn't have a
tough decision to make.

00:26:52.890 --> 00:26:55.410
I was leaving the next day.

00:26:55.410 --> 00:26:56.477
But yeah.

00:26:56.477 --> 00:26:58.810
There's always been a lot of
speculation about the fire.

00:26:58.810 --> 00:27:04.590
But basically what happened
was, like I was saying,

00:27:04.590 --> 00:27:09.339
we were building a
new addition to the--

00:27:09.339 --> 00:27:11.005
we had put on another
shipping container

00:27:11.005 --> 00:27:15.000
and the bar was going to
extend out to the right side.

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:18.000
And then there was going to
be a little secret garden

00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:20.140
on the side patio.

00:27:20.140 --> 00:27:27.630
And they had just put in a glass
screen door, which is now still

00:27:27.630 --> 00:27:31.420
on the shipping container
that's in a different spot.

00:27:31.420 --> 00:27:33.900
But what they failed to
take into consideration

00:27:33.900 --> 00:27:37.290
was that that screen
door was completely

00:27:37.290 --> 00:27:42.450
shielded off from Michigan
and also from 17th.

00:27:42.450 --> 00:27:49.750
So anyone could easily come
and not be seen from that side.

00:27:49.750 --> 00:27:52.980
So what happened was,
there was a series

00:27:52.980 --> 00:27:54.270
of break-ins that night.

00:27:54.270 --> 00:27:57.210
The first one was at
Nemo's down the street.

00:27:57.210 --> 00:28:01.506
And someone went in, smashed the
window, stole a bunch of booze.

00:28:01.506 --> 00:28:03.380
And then a little bit
later that night, there

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:06.330
was a break-in at our place.

00:28:06.330 --> 00:28:11.130
So someone had smashed
that screen window,

00:28:11.130 --> 00:28:13.200
went into that
shipping container,

00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:18.420
and then broke the window
to get into the restaurant.

00:28:18.420 --> 00:28:23.370
And again, no one's going to
see this or hear it happening.

00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:27.540
Went in and stole pretty
much all the booze

00:28:27.540 --> 00:28:33.370
within arm's reach, and
ran out the back door.

00:28:33.370 --> 00:28:38.480
They found one of the
bags of booze out there.

00:28:38.480 --> 00:28:46.590
And we have a little tip safe
up at the counter, where,

00:28:46.590 --> 00:28:48.640
actually, the fire started.

00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:51.660
They tried to-- they
smashed it open with an axe

00:28:51.660 --> 00:28:58.230
that we had by our smoker
that we used to split wood

00:28:58.230 --> 00:29:00.420
to put it into the smoker.

00:29:00.420 --> 00:29:04.170
So it was someone who
was familiar with--

00:29:04.170 --> 00:29:07.700
who had walked around
in the neighborhood,

00:29:07.700 --> 00:29:11.970
to know that that wood
splitter was there,

00:29:11.970 --> 00:29:17.490
to know that that
entrance had literally,

00:29:17.490 --> 00:29:21.700
two days before the fire,
just been installed.

00:29:21.700 --> 00:29:26.190
So as someone-- yeah,
someone in the area.

00:29:26.190 --> 00:29:32.010
And then they started a fire
at the host stand, which

00:29:32.010 --> 00:29:35.690
why they did, we don't know.

00:29:35.690 --> 00:29:39.660
The speculation that we
have is at the host stand

00:29:39.660 --> 00:29:44.040
was where we have
the stereo equipment.

00:29:44.040 --> 00:29:47.070
And so our thought
was that they probably

00:29:47.070 --> 00:29:50.880
thought that that was a camera
system, because it's not clear

00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:52.410
that it's stereo.

00:29:52.410 --> 00:29:55.440
And so that was
all wood encased.

00:29:55.440 --> 00:30:00.720
So they started a fire there
and it ran out the back door.

00:30:00.720 --> 00:30:02.390
There was a witness.

00:30:02.390 --> 00:30:05.860
There was a suspect.

00:30:05.860 --> 00:30:09.370
And I believe that there
was someone brought

00:30:09.370 --> 00:30:13.480
into custody that said that
they broke in but didn't

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:15.040
start the fire.

00:30:15.040 --> 00:30:19.430
But there's no proof linking
them to the whole thing.

00:30:19.430 --> 00:30:19.930
But--

00:30:19.930 --> 00:30:22.150
SPEAKER: It's still
an unsolved mystery.

00:30:22.150 --> 00:30:24.608
BRAD GREENHILL: It's an unsolved
mystery, as far as I know.

00:30:24.608 --> 00:30:28.900
I haven't checked in
on it for a long time.

00:30:28.900 --> 00:30:30.720
You know, right
afterwards, you're

00:30:30.720 --> 00:30:33.040
like, you want to
catch the person.

00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:36.010
And then you start realizing
that more than likely,

00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:41.460
the person who did
this was like--

00:30:41.460 --> 00:30:46.390
there's no-- the punishment
doesn't fit the crime, kind of.

00:30:46.390 --> 00:30:50.920
Like, what-- it's not going
to bring the restaurant back.

00:30:50.920 --> 00:30:55.000
This guy's life
already is not good.

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:58.960
You know, he's probably
homeless, alcoholic.

00:30:58.960 --> 00:31:02.860
In a lot of ways, this is--

00:31:02.860 --> 00:31:06.160
if he goes to jail, his life
will probably be better.

00:31:06.160 --> 00:31:06.660
You know?

00:31:06.660 --> 00:31:07.307
SPEAKER: Yeah.

00:31:07.307 --> 00:31:08.640
BRAD GREENHILL: Debatable, but--

00:31:08.640 --> 00:31:09.223
SPEAKER: Yeah.

00:31:09.223 --> 00:31:10.960
Trials and
tribulations, for sure.

